This program works in vanilla processing 1.5.1:

``` java
int x = 0;
int y = 0;

void setup() {
  size(200, 200);
  noLoop();
}

void draw() {
  background(226);
  x++;
  y++;
  ellipse(x, y, 10, 10);
}

void mouseClicked() {
  redraw();
}
```

So I think it's really a bug.

Processing sources has folllowing code in `size()` method:

``` java
SwingUtilities.invokeLater(new Runnable() {
      public void run() {
        // Set the preferred size so that the layout managers can handle it
        setPreferredSize(new Dimension(iwidth, iheight));
        setSize(iwidth, iheight);
      }
    });
```

So actual `setSize` will be called in other thread and if you call `(width)` or `(height)` from setup fn there is race condition between current thread and swing thread. This case can me manually handled in quil but it will be pretty messy.

As I see, the main problem here is this native libs that need to added to resources folder. But we want to pack them into jars so they can be easily included in project.clj... 
